article.headline: N.Y. nearly squanders 16-point lead
article.linkText: Liberty hold off Comets for fifth straight win
article.story:
HOUSTON (AP) -- Becky Hammon helped the New York Liberty hang on
to make it five wins in a row.

Hammon scored six of her 13 points down the stretch to keep New
York from blowing a 16-point, second-half lead and beat the Houston
Comets 71-62 Thursday night.

"We got a little careless in the second half and that is
something you can't do against the Houston Comets," Hammon said.
"We were able to get back into it, but we really had to battle
back to get into this game. We like to play in close situations and
that is what we were able to do tonight."

Elena Baranova also had 13 points to help the Liberty beat
Houston for the second time in 10 days.

After the Comets took a 53-52 lead with 7:21 to go, Hammon led
the way with six points and helped the Liberty (5-1) close the game
with a 19-9 run.

Sheryl Swoopes scored a game-high 19 points for the Comets, who
lost their second straight game and fell to 1-2 at home.

"It's tough to walk out of here with an 'L' today," Swoopes
said. "But hopefully we will learn from this and bounce back on
Saturday with a win."

Tina Thompson added 13 points and Michelle Snow added 12 points
and seven rebounds for Houston (3-4).

The Liberty, who lost their first game of the season at Indiana,
beat the Comets 68-62 on May 23 at Madison Square Garden.

New York took a 44-28 lead with an 8-3 run to start the second
half.

Tari Phillips, who scored 11 points, made a pair of layups,
including a reverse with 17:03 left, to give the Liberty a 16-point
lead, their biggest of the game.

But Houston responded with a 21-6 run and took its second lead
of the game when Swoopes hit a 17-foot jumper with 8:01 left.

"We did everything until Swoopes started making everything from
heaven," Liberty coach Richie Adubato said. "But we withstood it
all and kept our composure which is what you have to do in the pro
game."
